│ Evidence brief: TP53 shows no significant genetic association with coronary  │
│ artery disease (CAD) in GWAS (p = 0.42, OR = 1.02), indicating weak support  │
│ for a causal role in cardiovascular pathology. Expression data reveal low    │
│ TP53 levels in heart tissue (TPM = 2.1), suggesting limited on-target        │
│ biological activity in the cardiovascular system. Literature confirms that   │
│ TP53 is a well-established tumor suppressor with no established              │
│ cardiovascular function, and its direct pharmacological targeting remains    │
│ highly challenging due to its structural and functional complexity. While    │
│ TP53 is highly expressed in tumor microenvironments, its low cardiac         │
│ expression and lack of mechanistic rationale for cardiovascular benefit      │
│ raise significant feasibility and safety concerns. Prior art highlights that │
│ successful cardiovascular targets (e.g., PCSK9) have clear biological roles  │
│ in lipid metabolism and vascular homeostasis—conditions not met by TP53.     │
